  "title": "Buttons and Pockets",
  "description": "What if clowns created the universe? What's the connection between juggling and astrophysics? Can we sew up the Fabric of Spacetime into a stylish new suit?! Buttons &amp; Pockets is a fable about creativity, the cosmos, &amp; how we weave science and art into the fabric of reality. For kids, physicists, &amp; the young at heart.",
  "credits": "<strong>Playwright</strong>: Aaron Pickett / Marya Folinsbee<br/><strong>Director</strong>: Aaron Pickett / Marya Folinsbee<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Aaron Pickett, Marya Folinsbee<br/><strong>Designers</strong>: Marya Folinsbee<br/>",
  "website": "https://materialtheatre.ca | @material_theatre",
  "plain_language": "Buttons and Pockets follows Pockets, a clumsy fashion designer, as she teams up with a superstar named Buttons to create a whole new universe. Together, they tackle creative roadblocks and cosmic puzzles to design a beautiful space-time.",
